<i>Hey, what the hell
is that kid doing there?</i>

01:07:06.952 --> 01:07:09.872
<i>There are two basic styles...</i>

01:07:09.997 --> 01:07:14.585
- He's still got my thumb.
- His thumb's OK.

01:07:14.710 --> 01:07:15.919
Ready? Go!

01:07:19.175 --> 01:07:21.260
Watch your position!

01:07:31.353 --> 01:07:34.106
- Winner, Harry Bosco!
- Yeah!

01:07:35.983 --> 01:07:37.484
Winner!

01:07:38.986 --> 01:07:42.364
<i>On table number two,
Lincoln Hawk and John Grizzly!</i>

01:07:42.489 --> 01:07:46.118
<i>This should be a tough match.
Grizzly's getting him over the top.</i>

01:07:46.243 --> 01:07:49.914
<i>Grizzly looks like he's got
Linc Hawk in trouble.</i>

01:08:43.803 --> 01:08:47.305
John Grizzly is our winner.
Grizzly has won again.

01:08:47.430 --> 01:08:50.977
And the newcomer, Lincoln Hawk,
has lost his first finals match.

01:08:51.102 --> 01:08:53.312
Remember, ladies and gentlemen.

01:08:53.437 --> 01:08:58.609
This is a double elimination. Each of these
semifinalists have another chance.

01:08:58.734 --> 01:09:01.654
You have to lose twice
to be out of the competition.

01:09:10.290 --> 01:09:13.960
Get him up to my suite.
I wanna talk to him.

01:09:15.044 --> 01:09:18.214
Yeah. A little harder.

01:09:19.465 --> 01:09:21.843
I hope I didn't tear anything.

01:09:23.720 --> 01:09:25.430
Yeah, that's better.

01:09:28.224 --> 01:09:30.100
- Hawk?
- What do you want?

01:09:30.225 --> 01:09:35.814
Mr Cutler wants a word with you.
He's waiting in the presidential suite.

01:09:37.108 --> 01:09:38.359
- Ed?
- Yeah.

01:09:38.484 --> 01:09:42.906
- How long before I go on again?
- You got about a half-hour.

01:09:43.031 --> 01:09:44.448
I'll be there.

01:09:56.044 --> 01:09:57.589
Come in, Hawk.

01:10:00.800 --> 01:10:04.429
You want a drink?
You don't have to stay sharp.

01:10:05.430 --> 01:10:09.309
I understand you already
lost your first match.

01:10:09.434 --> 01:10:14.105
- What do you want, Cutler?
- We don't have to be enemies.

01:10:16.191 --> 01:10:18.985
I never wanted to be your enemy.

01:10:19.110 --> 01:10:22.364
All right, then. Let's get right to it.

01:10:24.449 --> 01:10:27.452
With Christina gone...

01:10:27.577 --> 01:10:32.332
I have no family left in my life,
except for Michael.

01:10:33.208 --> 01:10:36.962
You never had anything,
so you have nothing to lose.

01:10:37.838 --> 01:10:41.258
Hawk, you can believe what you want to.

01:10:41.383 --> 01:10:46.096
But you're a deserter, plain and simple.
You deserted your wife and your son.

01:10:46.221 --> 01:10:47.889
You were tearing us apart.

01:10:48.014 --> 01:10:51.687
Don't try to clear your conscience
at my expense.

01:10:51.812 --> 01:10:55.858
You're a liar. You deserted them.

01:10:57.609 --> 01:11:01.363
- Are you finished?
- I'm not through with you yet.

01:11:02.531 --> 01:11:07.744
Come on outside.
I want to show you something. Come on!

01:11:20.257 --> 01:11:24.303
Down there in the parking lot
in front of the hotel.

01:11:24.428 --> 01:11:28.807
That's the finest rig that money can buy.
If you want it, it's yours.

01:11:30.100 --> 01:11:34.062
Here's a cheque for $500,000.
Take it and get the hell out of my life.

01:11:34.188 --> 01:11:38.400
What are you trying to do? I gave you
custody of the boy, I signed papers.

01:11:38.525 --> 01:11:41.445
- What more do you want?
- I'm making things easy for you.

01:11:41.570 --> 01:11:44.533
You don't need Michael
as a meal ticket any more.

01:11:44.658 --> 01:11:49.163
So take the truck, take the money.
Start a new life. Start your own family!

01:11:49.288 --> 01:11:50.706
I got a family.

01:11:52.791 --> 01:11:55.878
When this is over, I'm coming to get him.

01:11:57.630 --> 01:12:02.218
- You're going back on your word.
- Yeah.

01:12:02.343 --> 01:12:05.888
You signed over custody. He'll never
go with you because you're a loser.

01:12:06.013 --> 01:12:08.224
You've always been a loser!

01:12:10.100 --> 01:12:15.564
- Mr Cutler is talking to you.
- I'm through talking.

01:12:30.371 --> 01:12:34.333
<i>We continue
with our semifinal series of matches.</i>

01:12:34.458 --> 01:12:38.172
<i>- You're mine.
- This is a double elimination tournament.</i>

01:12:38.297 --> 01:12:42.343
<i>Any competitor who loses twice out
of the eight on these four tables...</i>

01:12:42.468 --> 01:12:45.763
I'm going through you
like gas through a funnel.

01:12:54.772 --> 01:12:58.025
<i>You're mine, mister.</i>

01:12:58.776 --> 01:13:02.154
- Get him off of my thumb.
- Keep your elbow in the cup!

01:13:02.280 --> 01:13:04.615
- I don't see it.
- Put your elbow in the cup!

01:13:04.740 --> 01:13:07.577
I don't see it.

01:13:07.702 --> 01:13:09.036
Ready? Go!

01:13:35.607 --> 01:13:41.487
<i>Mad Dog Madison will be
the next opponent for Linc Hawk.</i>

01:13:44.407 --> 01:13:48.912
<i>Bull Hurley has beaten Harry Bosco
and Bull Hurley goes on to the finals.</i>

01:13:52.582 --> 01:13:56.920
<i>Carl Adams. Carl Adams is our winner.
Carl Adams goes on to the finals.</i>

01:14:02.425 --> 01:14:07.263
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, we're ready for
the last matches of the semifinal series.</i>

01:14:07.388 --> 01:14:09.557
<i>The winners go on to the finals.</i>

01:14:09.682 --> 01:14:12.018
<i>Over here, we have Mad Dog Madison...</i>

01:14:24.324 --> 01:14:25.825
Come on! Come on!

01:14:30.288 --> 01:14:33.291
Winner, Lincoln Hawk!

01:14:33.416 --> 01:14:36.169
<i>Linc Hawk has beaten Mad Dog Madison!</i>

01:14:36.294 --> 01:14:39.756
<i>And Linc Hawk goes on to the finals.</i>

01:14:39.881 --> 01:14:42.551
Next cab. Move it up.

01:14:46.513 --> 01:14:50.267
<i>We're approaching
the most important event</i>

01:14:50.392 --> 01:14:52.811
<i>of this unique and exciting competition.</i>

01:14:52.936 --> 01:14:57.023
The final phase in the world of arm
wrestling. We call this "Over the Top".

01:14:58.358 --> 01:15:01.570
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
let's bring on our four finalists.</i>

01:15:01.695 --> 01:15:06.783
Our first finalist, from Jacksonville,
Florida, undefeated in five years.

01:15:06.908 --> 01:15:09.202
Let's bring him on. Bull Hurley!

01:15:25.721 --> 01:15:31.351
His opponent, two-time Canadian
champion, Slammin' Carl Adams!

01:15:34.563 --> 01:15:38.984
From Boston, pride of
the teamsters, Harry Bosco.

01:15:45.157 --> 01:15:50.037
And finally, the newcomer from the
independent truckers, Lincoln Hawk!

01:16:03.592 --> 01:16:05.427
Whoo!

01:16:06.178 --> 01:16:10.893
Ladies and gentlemen, let's give our
four finalists a big round of applause!

01:16:12.645 --> 01:16:16.565
<i>- I can't lose, Hawk.
- Shut up!</i>

01:16:16.690 --> 01:16:18.817
- Say it, man.
- Get your elbows down.

01:16:18.943 --> 01:16:23.030
I can't lose. Come on, let's go.
I can't lose, Hawk.

01:16:23.155 --> 01:16:27.952
Linc Hawk is trying to stay calm,
but inside you know he has to be boiling.

01:16:28.077 --> 01:16:33.999
Look at him, ladies and gentlemen. A lot
of talking to the referee going on, too.

01:16:34.124 --> 01:16:36.752
Dad, over here!

01:16:40.214 --> 01:16:41.841
Dad! Go, Dad!

01:16:41.966 --> 01:16:43.884
- First you, then Hurley.
- Three fouls!

01:16:44.009 --> 01:16:47.888
- I'm psyching up the son of a bitch.
- I'm the ref. Get your elbow in there!

01:16:48.013 --> 01:16:50.224
- Dad!
- Michael, come with me.

01:16:50.349 --> 01:16:55.312
Come here, Michael! Michael,
come here! Stop! Come back.

01:16:55.437 --> 01:16:59.191
Ready? Go!

01:17:02.027 --> 01:17:04.407
<i>...he wears him out.</i>

01:17:04.532 --> 01:17:05.992
<i>OK, ladies and gentlemen.</i>

01:17:06.117 --> 01:17:09.287
<i>Bull Hurley and Carl Adams
going at it right over there.</i>

01:17:09.412 --> 01:17:10.621
Come on, man!

01:17:14.584 --> 01:17:16.335
Get your shoulders square.

01:17:16.460 --> 01:17:22.216
I'm not gonna start until we got it squared.
Lock it back. Ready? Go!

01:17:22.341 --> 01:17:24.594
Winner - Lincoln Hawk!

01:17:27.096 --> 01:17:29.640
- I wasn't ready yet!
- It was fair! You lost!

01:17:29.765 --> 01:17:35.104
Man, I wasn't ready! Hey, I've been
cheated! I wasn't ready, I said!

01:17:35.229 --> 01:17:37.648
Set it off, man!

01:17:41.986 --> 01:17:44.530
- No!
- Yeah!

01:17:44.655 --> 01:17:47.992
<i>Bull Hurley goes on to the
final match of the competition.</i>

01:18:00.423 --> 01:18:03.384
Dad! Dad!

01:18:03.509 --> 01:18:06.846
Mike, what are you doing here? Huh?

01:18:06.971 --> 01:18:09.933
- I had to see you.
- How'd you get here?

01:18:10.058 --> 01:18:15.230
Dad, it's a long story,
but, listen, I want to stay with you.

01:18:16.064 --> 01:18:19.359
- Mike, do you?
- Yeah.

01:18:19.484 --> 01:18:25.406
I want you to stay too, but I don't think
your grandfather is gonna let that happen.

01:18:25.532 --> 01:18:28.701
But I want to be with you, Dad.

01:18:28.826 --> 01:18:34.582
I want to be with you too, but, Mike,
I don't have any money. I sold the truck.

01:18:34.707 --> 01:18:37.710
That's OK. You're going to win
like you said, remember?

01:18:37.835 --> 01:18:41.839
You'll win that big old truck
and you can start your own business.

01:18:45.635 --> 01:18:49.474
Mike, in this last match
I... I think I pulled a little too hard.

01:18:49.599 --> 01:18:52.727
I'm...

01:18:52.853 --> 01:18:57.858
And this guy I'm going against, Bull
Hurley, he hasn't lost in about five years,

01:18:57.983 --> 01:19:02.279
and... I don't know, he's... he's good, Mike.

01:19:02.404 --> 01:19:08.201
He's real good and... I just don't know.

01:19:11.872 --> 01:19:14.291
Are you saying you're gonna lose?

01:19:16.543 --> 01:19:18.712
I might.

01:19:23.633 --> 01:19:25.927
I don't believe this.

01:19:26.052 --> 01:19:30.015
All that talk about never giving up
was all lies. You never believed it.

01:19:30.140 --> 01:19:34.311
And what you said to me, remember?
Now is the time to do it for yourself.

01:19:34.436 --> 01:19:37.814
The world meets nobody halfway.
If you want it, you take it.

01:19:37.939 --> 01:19:40.066
- Mike.
- You weren't talking about me,

01:19:40.192 --> 01:19:42.487
you were talking about yourself.

01:19:42.613 --> 01:19:46.200
- Mike, please.
- Now is your chance, Dad, don't you see?

01:19:46.325 --> 01:19:50.495
I don't care about what happened before,
so stop trying to prove yourself.

01:19:50.621 --> 01:19:56.210
It doesn't matter if you win or lose, Dad.
I don't care about that.

01:19:57.044 --> 01:20:01.465
All I care about is being with you, Dad.

01:20:01.590 --> 01:20:06.261
- I love you.
- I love you too, Mike.

01:20:08.180 --> 01:20:10.724
We'll try, OK?

01:20:12.017 --> 01:20:14.478
That's a big guy.

01:20:14.603 --> 01:20:18.524
<i>- Well, so are you.
- Ladies and gentlemen, the final match.</i>

01:20:24.571 --> 01:20:29.284
The referees from the International
Arm Wrestling Council.

01:20:33.664 --> 01:20:39.797
The finalist, undefeated in five years,
five-time world champion, Bull Hurley.

01:20:44.760 --> 01:20:49.807
And, ladies and gentlemen, the sole
remaining challenger, Lincoln Hawk,

01:20:49.932 --> 01:20:53.143
the man who has surprised
everybody here today.

01:20:53.269 --> 01:20:57.022
If you want it, you gotta take it.

01:21:02.152 --> 01:21:04.488
- Challenger and champion.
- You're mine!

01:21:04.613 --> 01:21:09.785
Bull Hurley and Lincoln Hawk.
Or should we say David and Goliath?

01:21:09.910 --> 01:21:13.122
The winner here tonight
will walk out with the world cup,

01:21:13.247 --> 01:21:17.835
a $250,000 truck
from the Volvo White company,

01:21:17.960 --> 01:21:24.174
$100,000 in cash, and the title
of arm wrestling world champion.

01:21:24.300 --> 01:21:27.094
He doesn't belong
on my arm wrestling table.

01:21:27.219 --> 01:21:32.310
That's my area, that's my game.
He's got no shittin' business there.

01:21:32.435 --> 01:21:35.438
<i>Our two finalists are now
psyching each other out.</i>

01:21:35.563 --> 01:21:39.525
<i>Linc Hawk's giving away just
about 100 pounds to Bull Hurley.</i>

01:21:39.650 --> 01:21:42.403
<i>That's a lot to give away in arm wrestling.</i>

01:21:42.528 --> 01:21:44.739
- You're mine.
- Let's go.

01:21:44.864 --> 01:21:48.034
<i>- Yeah!
- Let the competition begin.</i>

01:21:48.159 --> 01:21:49.827
<i>- Yeah!
- May the best man win!</i>

01:21:49.952 --> 01:21:55.166
- Come on, chicken shit.
- Place your elbows here. Hawk, you too.

01:21:55.291 --> 01:21:59.503
What I do is, I just try to take my hat
and I turn it around,

01:21:59.629 --> 01:22:02.632
and it's like a switch that goes on.

01:22:02.757 --> 01:22:06.677
<i>And when the switch goes on,
I feel like another person, I feel...</i>

01:22:06.802 --> 01:22:10.890
I don't know, I feel like a...

01:22:11.015 --> 01:22:12.808
like a truck, like a machine.

01:22:12.934 --> 01:22:16.812
I own you. You've been
ducking me for years.

01:22:16.938 --> 01:22:19.690
You've got no chance. You know that?

01:22:19.815 --> 01:22:22.904
